  "texts": [
    "For Deep, Sift, GIST, and Text-to-Image, queries are randomly sampled from available query workloads.",
    "For SALD, ImageNet, and Seismic, 100 queries are randomly selected from the datasets and excluded from the index-building phase.For hardness experiments, we use Deep query vectors of varying complexity, denoted as a percentage ranging from 1% to 10%.",
    "These vectors were obtained by adding Gaussian noise (𝜇 = 0, 𝜎 2 ranging from 0.01 to 0.1) to randomly choose dataset vectors, with the percentage reflecting the 𝜎 2 value [167].",
    "The 100-query workloads for the power law distribution datasets are generated following the same distributions using different seeds.",
    "Unless otherwise stated, all experiments were conducted with 10-NN queries per the standard in the community [2, 8,126]."
  ],
